      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MIKI PINS NZ (8) resumes off some strong form last campaign including a fourth from the back row in the Victoria Cup two starts back. Readied with a trial and has won fresh before. Owns a decent record at this circuit and distance and finds a winnable assignment first up. BAINBRIDGE (9) has been racing well in good company, placing two back in the Newcastle Mile before a solid fifth from this same barrier in last week's G2 Light Horse FFA. He'll enjoy a class drop. THE ANSWER (5) faded out last week but came from this barrier when winning at this circuit and distance prior so is worth another chance. ALTA WILLIAM (6) was first up for two months when he came from the back row to win at Bathurst last start. Should be fitter for that so could go on with it. PERFECT STRIDE NZ (10) is back in winning form and can feature if things go his way from a wide draw.",
